Player

Player

Narrator

Lucian pulled out a folder and opened it.

Player

"I told you, Lucian, you're vice president now. You don't need to keep calling me 'sir'."

"I told you, Lucian, you're vice president now. Stop calling me 'sir'."

Lucian Galade

"Now that that's settled, I'll let you prepare for your rally."

Lucian Galade

"Before I begin, I have to ask if you're sure you wish to follow through on this investigation. After all, Tusk has been an ally throughout your term."

Player

"I don't care. Give me the dirt on Tusk."

Player

"Good point. Maybe I don't need to hear the results."

Lucian Galade

"Now that that's settled, I'll let you prepare for your rally."

Narrator

A few hours later, I was waiting in the wings at the Norsord Auditorium in Anrica. In the audience were several thousand of my conservative supporters.

Lucian Galade

"'I bless the Raynes down in Anrica.'"

Narrator

Anrica Mayor Curtan Leste gave a short introductory speech. I couldn't look at him without thinking about how I'd let Monica down.

Narrator

Everyone cheered as I walked onstage -- except for a scowling Mayor Curtan Leste. He had tried to escape my shadow by joining the NFP, only to be defeated once more when our parties became allies.

Narrator

Gloria gave a short speech introducing me. Then, it was my turn.
